        }
      ],
      "config_anomalies": [
        {
          "signal": "what was observed",
          "risk": "why this is a concern",
          "severity": "critical|high|medium|low"
        }
      ],
      "attack_surface": "one paragraph on attack vectors implied by this stack",
      "suggested_scanners": ["scanner names warranted by this stack"]
    }
  ],
  "cross_asset_patterns": [
    "observations that span multiple assets (shared infrastructure, common misconfig, etc.)"
  ]
}

Rules:
- Only include version_issues for REAL, well-known CVEs or security advisories. Do not fabricate.
- suggested_scanners: choose only from: cors, jwt, webcontent, dlp, graphql, oauth, apiversions,
  hostheader, websocket, nuclei, cms-plugins, aillm, jenkins, ratelimit, smuggling, cdnbypass, depconf.
- If a component version is not specific enough to identify vulnerabilities, omit version_issues for it.
- config_anomalies should only flag genuinely risky patterns, not cosmetic issues.

